---
title: Hibachi Sweet Soy Bavette Steak & Shrimp with Garlic Rice, Sesame-Roasted Zucchini & Spicy Special Sauce
description: Surf ’n’ turf meets hibachi-style cooking for this twist on a steakhouse classic. Bavette steaks are seared to form a satisfying crust, then sliced and piled over garlic rice along with spiced shrimp and sesame roasted zucchini. Feeling saucy? Don’t worry—this dish has not one, but TWO sauces. A warm, sweet soy glaze is drizzled over the steak, while a creamy, spicy special sauce on the side is perfect for dipping each bite. Who needs a restaurant menu when you’ve got all that?
